Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
 • Gross Profit = 4,962,437.45  
 • Total Revenue = 18,062,437.45  
 • Calculation = (4,962,437.45 / 18,062,437.45) × 100% ≈ 27.47%

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
 • Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -13,358,400.82  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 1,903,121.89  
 • Calculation = -13,358,400.82 / 1,903,121.89 ≈ -7.01

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "27.47%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-7.01"
  }
}
